<Text>My son is the actual person who had gotten braces from DR S. Chong; son of the late DR L. Chong, who we also had the pleasure of meeting, but I would highly recommend DR S. Chong.  My son had a severe under bite that was completely corrected.
Pros: DR S. Chong is personable, friendly, and shows he likes the kids; the staff is also very helpful and understanding; procedure of getting the braces is explained in depth and not hurried; they give out after-care items needed to care for the braces freely, and if there is a issue with the braces, they quickly set time for your child to get seen. Although it is costly, they allow a payment plan that works for you.  They also have free parking in the back. Office is very clean, always. Easy to find corner location.
Cons: Not entirely their fault because insurance is a problem that plagues our nation, the co-payment is quite high; they have short hours, and limited schedule availability; braces are a long process, so your child will have to return for many visits for 2 to 3 years; and you might have to listen to your child complain initially until they become accustomed to it.
My son is so happy now that his teeth are straight. On to my other children.</Text><pictures>None< /pictures><rate>5<//rate><time>1519886275954<//time><Gmap_id>0x808f957b86117df3:0xfb76e4139848bcfc< /Gmap_id></record>

<Rating>5<//Rating><Review>Really, REALLY, good wings

I stopped in on a whim tonight and decided to try their "dry rubbed" chicken wings because I really don't like "wet" wings with sauce dripping off of them. I asked for ranch dressing because there's nothing like a dry wing dipped in something wet ... I think they're the best chicken wings I've ever had.

They're deep fried but that I think in super hot oil so they're crispy but not greasy. They're pretty decent-sized too. The "rub", kind of like seasoning salt, is tasty without being too spicy. The ranch dressing i got with them might be house made I'm not sure but it's a notch above the stuff that comes in a bottle from the supermarket. The wings also came with some carrot and celery sticks. It was a very enjoyable meal.

They have outdoor dining but my shop is just down the road so I got them to go.<//Review>< userid>
117410455807637940431</userid>

< Text>
Awesome BBQ takeout

Saw the special offering takeout of the BBQ dinner and ordered for delivery. This was great. Came with ribs, chicken, pulled pork, plenty of sauces, potato salad, beans, cornbread and coleslaw. Couldn't get any better than this. We had food for several meals. All of it delicious. My Wife doesn't normally touch coleslaw or potato salad and she loved them both. Plenty of bite to both of them.< /Text>

< Text>
Don't be fooled, this warehouse looking exterior in an industrial park houses a gem!  Stopped in on our way to Santa Cruz to catch the Warrior game and wait out the traffic. The place as packed, but a two nice young men gave our family of 4 their table.  Orders are placed at the bar. The guy was slammed but he was still friendly and helpful. He encouraged me to get the happy hour special pizza because it was a better value. He was working hard to serve everyone.   He even delivered our drinks and showed us where the soda machine was so we could get free refills.
The food was really good. We enjoyed the pizza, mac n' cheese, chicken quesadilla and a steak sandwich. Everything was tasty and hot.  For as busy as they were this was remarkable.
The game was great, the atmosphere was fun and we will surely visit again if we are back this way.< /Text>

I had to ask the guy to go over some parts and "DETAIL" the dirt and spots in the car... he seemed annoyed by me asking him to re-do it.. if you're looking for a quick wash, then go here. If you want a detail then go to Palms car wash or k street and Broadway in chula vista they are affordable and they do such a great job on the deatiling (which is what you are paying for)<//Text>

< review>
Dr. Cruz, Ina, Lily and the entire Rocky Ridge Family Dental Team were the most outstanding group I've had the pleasure of going to. This is the place to get rid of any dental anxiety! I came in with highly sensitive teeth (from another local practice who whitened and ground down my teeth without educating me on the residual effects), needing a bunch of fillings, a crown replacement, root planing, a cleaning, and referrals for 2 wisdom teeth and 2 implants.
Dr. Cruz was the most communicative, empathetic and educational doctor I've ever had. I swear he has a 6th (maybe 7th) sense when working on his patients' teeth because I never had a problem communicating to him while he fixed all of the above for me over the past year or so. He and team work together seamlessly and were so fun to be around, too. There was never an uncomfortable moment - my first visit was even while they were training a new assistant and Lily's care and positive instruction made me wish I worked with her, too (LOL). The front desk staff worked directly with me on billing and payments and always went over and ABOVE working with my ridiculous insurance company to make sure everything was covered that should be. Even with everything during this COVID-19 mess, the entire office took every safety measure imaginable to ensure the same service standards went unchanged. I have zero plans of ever going anywhere else - even just for advice now!< /review>

<GmapID>0x809b1ff0669e3bb9:0x8155aa4aab108b19< /GmapID><user_id>111013202289980168653<//user_id><date>1600805082666</date><Review>I wish I didn't ignore the bad reviews on this place! Please do not make the same mistake I did. My fiance' asked me before I set my first cleaning with them, "Can we please find a different dentist, I don't really like this place?" I ignored that too. I hope no one ignores my review.

Essentially, the reviews where they are more interested in the money and revenue than patient care is 100% accurate.  I can't say that they provide treatment plans that are not needed as other reviews mentioned, but I can say that they are more interested in the $ than patient care. So, I went in because one of my crowns randomly cracked on the bottom of one of my front teeth. I go in to get it fixed. After an X Ray the dentist comes in "I am going to have to do a whole new crown but I want to use (insert top of the line material) which is going to cost a bit more but will last longer than this one did". I agree that is fine, but I want to examine the cost. Then comes Sherry, she comes in and laughs and says "When you see me you know it means more money haha". Then tells me my insurance does not cover the cost of the crown but will cover the build up but it will cost me $1200 out of pocket. I thought that was a little high so I decided to call my insurance company myself. I explained what happened and they told me I would be responsible for my copay of $50 and up to $325 if I wanted the best material used. They then call Rocky Ridge (felicia) and Felicia says she will fill out the pre auth form with Delta Dental but it will take 72 hours. So, I wait 72 hours to get the update, and Sherry tells me "we never do pre authorization with HMO plans, as the fee schedule is illustrated in the plan". I agree with her then show her the plan where it shows my co pay options along with footnotes than clearly says

"The replacement of an existing inlay, onlay, crown, fixed partial denture (bridge)
or a removable full or partial denture is covered when:
a. The existing restoration/bridge/denture is no longer functional and cannot be
made functional by repair or adjustment, and
b. Either of the following:
- The existing non-functional restoration/bridge/denture was placed three or
more years prior to its replacement"

My initial crown was over 4 years ago. So I call Delta Dental to make sure I am interpreting this correctly, and of course I am. So Sherry says she will call Corporate on 9/18 and get back to me on 9/21. I don't hear back so I call today 9/22 and finally get an email saying Corporate wants me to pay out of pocket but I can file a grievance later with insurance to get my money back. I am not going through this. There whole thing is that "your coverage only covers decay" That is clearly wrong as I asked my insurance company what they cover and they do cover for causes of decay but they also cover restoration replacements over 3 years old and that is what my deal is. Also the initial crown is from when I took a bat to the mouth 4 years ago and they covered everything even though that was "cosmetic", same insurance company, same policy, different dentist. BEWARE WHEN LOOKING FOR A DENTIST!!!

Sherry mentioned multiple times" we can't charge you $350 because it cost us more in material". I don't know what to tell you, because that is what Delta Dental is telling me and they are the insurance company, bill them.  I get it, as a small business owner, all businesses need to make a profit but I don't like to be lied to and feel deceived when going to a medical office. I shouldn't have the same feeling of a used car salesman with my dentist.</Review><name>Jon Gay< /name>< response>

I'm very disappointment with how much resistance I'm getting from the staff for having my daughter in coed soccer. For starters I don't think girls and boys should be separated for shots when they're only 6. Honestly my daughter did better then half the other kids at try outs. The disappointing part is that when I signed her up they suggested the all girls league. I declined and paid 75 because I understand the importance of being in coed sports. Then at try outs they asked again if I wanted to switch her. Just last night someone called me from the recreation center telling me I only paid 10 so she has to be in the girls league. I told him I paid 75 and she's staying where she's at. Fast Tire is exactly that. Fast. In and out in 15-20 minutes, unless they're super busy and everyone ahead of you is getting full tire changes, and extra things. Even then, they still have you taken care of as quickly as possible. They're friendly, have used tires at great prices and are one of the only places around to offer Nitrogen fills for your tires to extend tire life and reduce leaks. Reasonable pricing, repairs do cost you if you didn't buy the tire from them, but it won't break your bank. Nor do they offer you things you don't need. You tell them what you're looking for, they give you options, no hassle. I highly recommend them!</text>

Listen up world this is the only place you need to go to when your car, van, suv or truck needs help!!!
The remarkably clean and professional staff especially including their stellar manager Ms Nicole whom will educate you on any issues, questions comments, or concerns in such a manner it leaves one feeling protected and well cared about by the right people.
Seriously I must say proudly I was truly impressed by all the wonderful technicians and with most regards to the polite professional gentleman there service advisor Mr Michael Kerekes who set my repair plans by accommodating both my schedule and bank account by taking care of my repairs WAY UNDER BUDGET I LOVE this beautiful shop!!!
If your vehicle is broke take it to Woodland Body Works this direct repair shop has the most honest enjoyable atmosphere I have ever seen in the auto repair industry- My experience can only be described as a symphony of superb customer service!!!!
Bringing my Mercedes Benz GL450 to Woodland Body Works was the best decision I could have made in getting it repaired to better than new condition.
Bradford Seguine

< Review>
This has been an overdue review of our overall experience at The Cottage Pet Hospital.
Which has been a pleasant experience from the moment I picked up my phone to call and investigate pricings and booking an appointment. I was greeted by Liz , she took her time in answering all of my questions over the phone. She seemed calmed and pleasant and very informative.

My dog was hit by a car the Thursday before a holiday weekend (a tragic accident occurred and technically both my dogs were hit the same night but I won't go into detail in this review).   He was less than a year old and weighed 6lbs. The only vets open were ER vets.  He needed surgery immediately and the cost of surgery at the ER vet was astronomical.  Cottage Pet hospital went above and beyond to help me and my 8month old rescue, Bradley.  The assistant who answered the phone said she wanted to call the doctor (on his day off) to see what they could do.  Minutes later the doctor called and told me he wanted to help and was going to find a way to get the surgery done despite the fact that they would be closed in addition to several other hurdles that made the task seem impossible to me.  I couldn't believe what I was hearing and I wondered whether everything would work out as the dr explained.  It did.  Because the doctor cared more about my dogs life than profit, today I have a fully functional healthy 18month old.  I'm convinced that there is a special place in heaven for people this who value life and health and will do ALL they can to save it.  I can't thank cottage per hospital enough.  They are the kindest people I've met and have the best place to bring my pets.< /Text>

A different nurse answered the door, raised her voice at me that the power was already shut down and everyone had left, and shut the door in my face as I explained we had JUST CALLED to confirm it was okay to show up 5 min late. It wasn't even 5 minutes past close.

We absolutely loved this vet up until then and never came back. If it wasn't for this instance I would give 5 stars.

Pros are:
+ Dr. Sahai is wonderful and absolutely amazing at diagnosis while being practical about cost (aka without going into debt)
+ If you are upfront in a polite manner or are like me and super stressed when you pet is sick (and have a million questions), the nurses will do whatever they can to help
+ No appointments needed on weekends for shots, it's a quick and easy
+ (Most) of the staff seem to really love pets and care about their well-being! Our pets love people and bond with the staff when they are in for treatment, which we really love and puts us at ease

Cons:
- There is a sarcastic doctor here that we do not jive well with, we feel she is not as straightforward when we ask her questions and she will often joke to us about how she never brings in her pets to the vet and just lets stuff in their bodies "work out on their own" (how is that professional).

- They never remember my pet insurance covers flea medicine! Every time I come in and buy it, I have to pay full price and then get my insurance to work with Cottage Pet Hospital on proactively applying my discount and refunding me the rest. < rating>
4</rating>
< Text>
Cottage Pet Hospital offers a warm atmosphere and caring staff in convenient location for local residents.

Pet Treatment: I brought my cat in for treatment after she started scooting across the carpet. Without getting into details the diagnosis was quick and treatment was effective.

Facility: There is a strong smell in this facility similar to most animal shelters I've been in. The staff do constantly clean but the building is dated and may have absorbed years of patient odors. I often see the staff cleaning and disinfecting after each patient and they are currently remodeling the facility so hopefully they will be able to reduce the smell.

Price: The prices for treatment seem comparable to that of Banfield Pet Hospitals found in most Petsmarts. They also seem to accept most insurance plans.

Parking: Since this is a small clinic parking is limited and street side parking is typically taken my near by residents. However, there is usually at least one or two spots open from my experience.<//Text>

< review>
I have never been to this hospital for visits. My 8 year old yorkie, Rocky, recently passed away. My friend found the hospital on her phone and called asking about burial service. The receptionist was very helpful. She gave us all the information and directions to the hospital. We had 15 mins to make it at the 630pm cut off time. When we arrived they were very sweet and sympathatic. I was too upset to talk and my friend had to handle everything for me. I am so thankful for everyone in the hospital. <Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
I've been a BMW owner since I got my License which was a very long time ago. Each time I've had some "awkward" or weird level of service at other BMW dealers. I heard raving reviews about Peter Pan BMW and I told myself that I will give it another try at Peter Pan BMW since they have the best reviews. I was beyond impressed by this dealer. I was taken care of from the moment my daughter and I walked in. I was greeted by Jim (nicest and most professional human being ever) He gave my daughter and the best greeting ever. Then he asked me detailed questions on what I was looking for and shared his thoughts with me. Since I had contacted this dealer ahead of time he had already had his homework done. He understood my concerns about staying within budget. I was impressed. Since at other dealers once you walk in you automatically become a target for the sales person next commission and they could care less what my needs are. At Peter Pan BMW it was such an incredible experience to know that they actually value me as a person. Then I was introduced to Javed the salesperson who was absolutely amazing. We went over our concerns in detail and he literally showed me 10 different scenarios to make sure that I am getting the best deal. He didn't try to pull a fast one one me like other BMW dealers always do! While we were going through my options and scenarios other members of the team (wish I could remember their names) introduced themselves  and they offered coloring books and other fun activities. I was so shocked. We even watched one of the salesperson granddaughters video which was so cute and it really touched our hearts. My daughter was so impressed now she wants to go there all the time now. As we were going through each of these details Jim was touching base with us each time to see if we were okay and if we needed anything. I personally saw that they were very busy, but they had made each of us customers feel like loyalty. I was able to select the 2020 BMW 530i Sedan  which is very beautiful and I know it fits my personality. < review>
TLDR: The sales people can be rude, only allow 5-10 minute test drives.

At first, the sales people at Peter Pan seemed very nice and accommodating. I scheduled an appointment for a test drive the day before, and we only waited a short time (10-15 min) for someone to see us. They were very friendly and gave us the keys and told us to take the car out - no further guidance.

We really enjoyed the test drive, it confirmed We liked the car and helped us learn which features were most important. We arrived back at the dealership about 30 minutes after driving off the lot. As soon as I entered, the salesman yelled from across the lobby that I almost got him fired before taking a call as I awkwardly stood there with the keys, and then continued to tell me that I had taken way too long. Apparently, test drives here should only last 5-10 minutes. I don‚Äôt think that is reasonable amount of time to figure out if you want to purchase a car. We were going to test out some other models, but the salesman kept harping on how we had almost gotten him fired and took way too long (despite being given absolutely no guidance beforehand). We decided it was not a good setting to make a major purchase and promptly left. I would look elsewhere before coming to this dealership.<//review>

<UserId.>102667470240553143281<//UserId.><review>I was promised a price for a BMW X4 and the next day, after I had gone through the trouble of finding a buyer for my old car and planning an 800 mile drive to Seattle (from California), I was told by the general manager of Peter Pan BMW that they are not going to honor their promised price. They said their sales representative hadn't confirm the price with the manager before promising it to me (as a client, I don't think I need to know that).

In case you are curious, the reason why we didn't close the deal the previous day was that we needed time to arrange for the delivery of the car to Seattle and to make sure that they could do that on the timeline at which we needed the car. The sales agent prepared all the paper work for the deal that we had agreed on and everything was ready for me to sign the next day.

Long story short, I ended up having to pay $2000 higher than their promised price to get the car, which, at that point, I had to do to avoid a full collapse of all my subsequent plans (with the sales of my old car and my trip to Seattle coming up). The general manager literally told me that they don't care what the client (i.e. I) was told the day before. He continued, if I had sigend the documents the night before he would have kept the lower price [read: wouldn't have been ABLE to change it to the higher price] but now he was not going to honor their own word.

That all said, the sales people were very helpful and considerate (I wish I could leave a separate rating for that). I think I got the manager on his bad day, but I expect a general manager of a big (and otherwise reputable) corporate like BMW not to pass the ongoing internal frictions and conflicts on to their clients.

I thought this was the end of the drama with the Peter Pan BMW and was glad that I didn't have to go back there again after I leave the lot ... But I was up for a big surprise!

At the noon of Oct 24th, I sold my old vehicle right outside of this dealership to buy the car from the Peter Pan BMW that I had sigend some of the documents for already (including the price breakdown agreement). As I was signijg the rest of the documents the manager came up and summoned the sales representative who was helping me sign the documents ... A few minutes later I was told that they were not going to sell the car to me because they had realized that I had left this review for them (I had posted the sections above this paragraph on Yelp the prior evening). This was utterly upsetting, but I will try to be professional an just write what I observed as opposed to how I feel.

Reading this whole note again, it is possible that the manager's ego couldn't handle the part that I said "[he] wouldn't have been ABLE to [cancel the sale if I had signed the documents]". So, CAUTION!! If, despite my experience, you decide to do business with this dealership make sure you understand that the managerial team here may have a delicate ego and, evidently, this is how they treat customers that they make unhappy, just to protect their delicate egos.< /review>< Time>

This review is mainly for the sales department and the salesman Doug Miller.  When I walked in, I already had my preconceived notions of pushy car salesmen and simply getting the "shorter end of the stick".  This, however, was not the case with Doug.  I went to Peter Pan having done a fair amount of research for the best deals on a certified pre-owned (cpo) X5.  Doug was more than patient and accommodating with my inquiries.  I left for that day with numbers, prices, and inventory to think about and to do more research and he gladly agreed to meet with me for any outstanding questions I might have had.  I was able to set up an appointment with him in 2 days and it was on that day that I had made my purchase for a cpo X5.  Because of Doug, I felt confident in my purchase and would recommend him to anyone looking for the best and honest deal from Peter Pan.
I took away one star because there was only one car key when I was promised 2 keys.  It took 1 month to get the 2nd key and then about a week to program it.
Aside from that, my experience at Peter Pan BMW  was first-class and I recommend asking for Doug Miller if you have the chance.</text>

I do not know a lot about cars, but had a feeling this just happened with the detailing process and when I stated this concern the salesman Norm stated it was not. I was in a hurry to get home and agreed to a $200 discount and I was still pretty excited about car and price. After  I was home I took to body shop and they stated that this was damage due to buffing too close and they had put wax over it to try and cover it up- worse off, very expensive to fix.
I have to say that I was really happy with everything, Norm was nice and so was the rest of the staff, and the car is great, but now I can only notice this scuff that was not there prior to the detailing.
Having said that I would advise taking pictures of your car prior to any work, and do not let them detail the car as they have inexperienced people doing this.</text>

< Review>
What can I possibly say about these scumbags that isn't already mentioned.  I've owned BMWs exclusively for over a decade and I've been to dealerships all over the country.  Nowhere will you find such incompetence than here.

I brought in my 2012 335i for a maintenance and an infrequent "Powertrain Malfunction".  It wasn't a big deal, it just popped up, you'd pull over, stop, restart....  it's going great.  This happened once or twice in a few months time.  I chalked it up to some recall or electronics or even getting some bad gas.  (Though, always premium.)

Cut to months later, I can barely drive the car 20 miles without it coming up.  And the car goes into limp mode when it happens, so on the freeway, I gotta maneuver out of the way.  Bring it in...  they all but call me a liar.  Finally, after getting video, they offer me $2k off the purchase of a new car.  You can get better than that on the website.  However, they never failed to try and upsell me when I was in on a service.  And, despite their dogged troubleshooting techniques, they never drove the car more than 1-3 miles.  Really bang up job guys.

To top it all off, I just want rid of this thing so I barely drive it for 9 months just waiting for the lease to expire.  I finally get the option to turn it in early, at my own cost, for the problems their warranty should have fixed.  But I was just sick of taking off work to go get it and deal with them.  On the way to literally drop the car off, it dies completely.

I was told by their "General Sales Manager" that there was nothing that would be done.  They didn't honor their warranty...  oh well.  And proceeded to try and sell me another.  Unbelievable.

The real shame is that it was a wonderful car until this.  And I've been a loving owner of so many for so long.  Now they just have me looking at other companies.

Well, that's enough for me.  I needed a hobby.  And my new hobby is telling everyone how terrible Peter Pan is.  Shouldn't be hard.< /Review>

< Text>
I purchased my BMW Certified Pre-owned 2012 Z4 from Peter Pan BMW in September 2015.  I noticed the front bumper had popped out from its plastic clips while it was parked in our garage a few days later.  We decided to wait until the first service to have these clips replaced.
Six months later while having my Z4 in for regular service, I brought to the attention of the service center mechanic the problem with my bumper constantly popping out, thinking it might need just clips replaced. They looked at it and suggested I bring the car back to the sales department.  I called and asked to speak to someone who could take a look at the problem.  Unfortunately it did not go as well as I would have expected.  Sales rep. Keith Ray was immediately defensive, accusative and downright condescending with me, blaming me for the damage and he never even looked at the car.  I then met with the sales Manager, Rob Rensen and he looked at bumper, but never once popped the hood open.  He said he would bring this up to the General Manager Jim Cyr for Peter Pan BMW and Rob asked that I call him back a few days later, which I did and left a voicemail.  I then called again the following week ‚Äì still no call back.  I emailed him directly and still no response.   Finally I got a hold of Rob over the phone a few weeks later only to give me the news that there is nothing that can be done because I waited too long to call back.
So much for the BMW certified Pre-Owned BMW program.  It is supposed to have been inspected by a BMW trained technician, but somehow they missed a few details, the biggest was the bracket that holds the front bumper, as it was almost failing when they sold it and did not want to stand behind their own car.
I took my BMW to my own certified mechanic and he ordered parts needed, it was a simple part replacement and not a complete replacement of the front bumper which is what Kevin and Rob presumed.   All it took was someone with some brains and a genuine interest in their customer to open the hood and really do a thorough check to find it was a simple inexpensive bracket replacement, in this case less than $30 dollars plus the labor to replace it.
I can live with that small cost to repair my car.  I am still very proud of it, but what I can't live with is the thought that others will be treated in pretty much the same way I was.  No one and I mean no one should be treated in a condescending and rude manner ever.
This is no way to conduct and/or run a business.  I won‚Äôt be taking my BMW to Peter Pan BMW as they have shown very clearly where they stand - a lack of basic knowledge and a lack of professional courtesy.< /Text>
